PELVIS

pelvis is the basin-shaped bony structure at the base of the spine
it transfers weight from the upper body through to the legs, cradles the lower abdominal organs, and provides the anchor for the powerful muscles of locomotion
pelvis is fadriel's foundation: when he stands, the load of his entire upper body passes through here

